<%- include('partials/header') %>

<style>
    /* Reset */
    * {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
        font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
        background: #f8fafc;
        color: #1e293b;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    /* Navbar */
    nav {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
        background: #1e293b;
        padding: 1rem 2rem;
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        z-index: 1000;
    }

    nav h2 {
        color: #fff;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    nav ul {
        list-style: none;
        display: flex;
        gap: 2rem;
    }

    nav ul li a {
        color: #fff;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 500;
        transition: color 0.3s ease;
    }

    nav ul li a:hover {
        color: #6838f8;
    }

    /* Hero Section */
    .hero {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 4rem 2rem;
        background: linear-gradient(to right, #647fed, #1518d3);
        color: #fff;
        border-radius: 0 0 2rem 2rem;
    }

    .hero h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .hero p {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
    }

    /* Content */
    .content {
        width: 90%;
        max-width: 1100px;
        margin: 3rem auto;
    }

    .content h2 {
        margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
        color: #1e293b;
        font-size: 1.8rem;
        border-left: 5px solid #38bdf8;
        padding-left: 10px;
    }

    /* Card Container */
    .card-container {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
        margin: 2rem 0;
    }

    .card {
        background: #fff;
        padding: 2rem;
        border-radius: 1rem;
        box-shadow: 0 6px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
    }

    .card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-8px);
        box-shadow: 0 12px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    }

    .card h3 {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        color: #2563eb;
    }

    .card ul {
        list-style: disc;
        padding-left: 1.2rem;
        color: #475569;
    }

    .content ul {
        margin-left: 1.5rem;
        color: #475569;
    }
    
    /* Two-column layout for project information */
    .project-section {
        margin: 3rem 0;
    }
    
    .project-header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }
    
    .project-header h2 {
        font-size: 2.2rem;
        color: #1e293b;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        border: none;
        padding: 0;
    }
    
    .project-header p {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        color: #475569;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }
    
    .two-column-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 2.5rem;
        margin: 2rem 0;
    }
    
    .column {
        background: #fff;
        padding: 2rem;
        border-radius: 1rem;
        box-shadow: 0 6px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }
    
    .column-header {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
        border-bottom: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
    }
    
    .column-icon {
        background: #2563eb;
        color: white;
        width: 40px;
        height: 40px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        margin-right: 1rem;
        font-weight: bold;
    }
    
    .column h3 {
        color: #1e293b;
        font-size: 1.4rem;
    }
    
    .objective-item, .scope-item {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f5f9;
    }
    
    .objective-item:last-child, .scope-item:last-child {
        border-bottom: none;
        margin-bottom: 0;
        padding-bottom: 0;
    }
    
    .objective-item h4, .scope-item h4 {
        color: #2563eb;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
    }
    
    .objective-item p, .scope-item p {
        color: #475569;
    }
    
    /* Overview section */
    .overview-container {
        background: #fff;
        padding: 2.5rem;
        border-radius: 1rem;
        box-shadow: 0 6px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        margin: 2.5rem 0;
    }
    
    .overview-container h3 {
        color: #1e293b;
        font-size: 1.6rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        text-align: center;
    }
    
    .overview-points {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
        gap: 1.5rem;
    }
    
    .overview-point {
        background: #f8fafc;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 0.75rem;
        border-left: 4px solid #2563eb;
    }
    
    .overview-point h4 {
        color: #2563eb;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
    }
    
    .overview-point p {
        color: #475569;
    }
    
    /* Responsive adjustments */
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
        .two-column-grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
        
        .overview-points {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
    }
</style>

<!-- Navbar -->
<nav>
    <h2>Data Privacy Hub</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">Research</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">Resources</a></li>
       
    </ul>

    
    <div class="two-column-grid">
        <div class="column">
            <div class="column-header">
                <div class="column-icon">A</div>
                <h3>Aim of the Research</h3>
            </div>
            <p>The research seeks to develop and recommend a comprehensive governance framework that enables educational institutions to benefit from artificial intelligence (AI) and big data analytics while protecting student privacy through proactive policies, technical safeguards, and increased cultural awareness.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="column">
            <div class="column-header">
                <div class="column-icon">S</div>
                <h3>Project Scope</h3>
            </div>
            <p>The project's scope is a thorough evaluation of the balance between exploiting data-driven technology for educational innovation and upholding strong ethical student data privacy safeguards. It attempts to create and promote a governance framework that allows educational institutions to use AI and big data analytics while protecting student privacy.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Project Objectives</h2>
    
    <div class="two-column-grid">
        <div class="column">
            <div class="column-header">
                <div class="column-icon">1</div>
                <h3>Primary Objectives</h3>
            </div>
            
            <div class="objective-item">
                <h4>Examine the Central Dilemma</h4>
                <p>To research the struggle between instructional technology innovation and student data privacy, examining potential risks and ethical issues.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="objective-item">
                <h4>Establish the Data Privacy Environment</h4>
                <p>To establish dominant concepts of educational data and data privacy policies, and to articulate the importance of safeguarding student data from legal, ethical, and trust perspectives.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="objective-item">
                <h4>Map the Regulatory Environment</h4>
                <p>To define and summarize primary student data privacy laws (FERPA, COPPA, GDPR) and detail their requirements for education institutions and technology providers.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="column">
            <div class="column-header">
                <div class="column-icon">2</div>
                <h3>Implementation Objectives</h3>
            </div>
            
            <div class="objective-item">
                <h4>Recommend a Proactive Governance Framework</h4>
                <p>To develop evidence-informed suggestions for institutions, including future-oriented ethical policy, technical security controls (e.g., "privacy by design"), operational controls (bias screening), and prioritizing continuous monitoring and cultural change.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="objective-item">
                <h4>Provide Practical Guidelines to Stakeholders</h4>
                <p>To give direction to teachers regarding data privacy and digital citizenship, and best practices for administrators in vendor management, policy development, and trust-building.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="overview-container">
        <h3>Project Overview</h3>
        <p>This research is a thorough examination of the crucial problem of striking a balance between student data privacy and technology innovation in contemporary educational settings.</p>
        
        <div class="overview-points">
            <div class="overview-point">
                <h4>Problem Definition</h4>
                <p>Describes the "double-edged sword" of privacy vs innovation, emphasising the moral and legal conflicts that educational institutions must resolve.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="overview-point">
                <h4>Analysing the Landscape</h4>
                <p>Giving a thorough overview of the concepts of educational data (demographic, academic, behavioural, and engagement), its applications, and the significance of safeguarding it.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="overview-point">
                <h4>Analysing the Legal Framework</h4>
                <p>Going over important privacy laws and rules (including COPPA, GDPR, and FERPA) that control how student data is handled and set criteria for districts and schools to comply with.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="overview-point">
                <h4>Putting Forward a Solution</h4>
                <p>Addressing the main study topic by promoting a multi-tiered governance architecture with proactive ethical policies, technical safeguards, operational measures, and cultural shift.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
</nav>

