<section class="content">
    <h2>What is Data Privacy?</h2>
    <p>Data privacy refers to the proper handling of personal information including how it's collected, stored, shared, and used.</p>
    
    <div class="card-container">
        <div class="card">
            <h3>For Students</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Control over academic records and personal information</li>
                <li>Protection from educational data misuse</li>
                <li>Rights to access and correct educational records</li>
                <li>Prevention of unauthorized sharing of academic performance</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h3>For Educational Institutions</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>FERPA compliance requirements</li>
                <li>Secure management of student records</li>
                <li>Ethical use of student data for educational purposes</li>
                <li>Preventing data breaches in educational systems</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Student Data Privacy Concerns</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Educational technology platforms collecting excessive data</li>
        <li>Third-party educational service providers accessing student information</li>
        <li>Long-term storage of academic records</li>
        <li>Sharing student data with research institutions without proper consent</li>
    </ul>
</section>

